<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-04T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00 Elections/84: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grummon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-04T10:00:00-05:00">June 4, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>95. President Roy has announced in a press interview published in the <hi rend="italic">Nouvelliste</hi> that the reconstitution of the
                            legislative chambers will take place in October; that until that time
                            the Council of State will be maintained and that modifications in the
                            present electoral law will be made early in July.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grummon</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>